               <msContents>
                  <summary>I-1) Maṣḥafa śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols.
                     2ra-4va)&#xD; I-2) Introductory exhortation and hymns (fols. 4va-6ra)&#xD; I-3)
                     ʾƎsaggǝd laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki... “I worship Thee…” (fols. 6rc-6va)&#xD; I-4)
                     Taʾāmra Māryām: 152 miracles (6va-108vb)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst wa-dǝngǝlt ba-kǝlʾe Māryām ... "O my Lady, Holy
                        and Two-fold Virgin Mary ..." (<locus target="#5rc">5rc-</locus>va)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos kahāli ... "O my Lady,
                        Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..." (<locus target="#5va">5va</locus>) (cp. ChRep n<locus target="#373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma bǝrhān ...
                        "Salutation to you, o my Lady Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the
                        Light ..." (<locus from="5va" to="6ra">5va-6ra</locus>).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Mary (Text I-4) are numbered.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
